                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/edpe-304" class="program-course-title">
              EDPE 304 Measurement and Evaluation (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-23908" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Educational&amp;Counselling Psych (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/608">Faculty of Education</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Ed Psych &amp; Couns (Psychology)              : The purposes of examinations. Causes of complaints about examinations. Equalizing means and dispersions in distribution of marks. Standardized scores. The percentile system. Essay and objective-type examinations. Taxonomies of educational objectives. Validity and reliability: item analysis.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
